!! Tags

|!Tag |!Applied to |
|<<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard">> |A dashboard tiddler (its body becomes the canvas) |
|<<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard/tile">> |A tile tiddler |
|<<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard/display-rule">> |A per-dashboard display rule (maps a target `filter` to the `field` matching tiles show) |

!! Dashboard fields

|!Field |!Meaning |
|`dashboard-id` |Stable id used to group tiles and build their titles. Optional — falls back to the dashboard title |

!! Tile fields

|!Field |!Meaning |
|`dashboard` |The owning dashboard's id (or title) |
|`target` |Title of the tiddler shown inside the tile (content tiles only) |
|`dash-parent` |Title of the group tile this tile lives inside. Empty / absent = top-level (directly on the dashboard canvas) |
|`role` |`group` for a group (meta) tile; empty / absent for an ordinary content tile |
|`caption` |Group tiles only — the editable group name shown in its header |
|`icon` |Group tiles only — an icon shown small before the caption when open; when collapsed //and// set, it becomes the group's whole header (hover shows the caption, click expands). Value is a tiddler title (transcluded) or inline markup. Set/cleared from the icon editor (group ⋮ menu → //Icon…//) |
|`collapsed` |Group tiles only — `yes` shows just the header bar, otherwise the group's canvas is shown |
|`x` / `y` |Top-left position in pixels, relative to the tile's container canvas |
|`w` / `h` |Width / height in pixels (both are retained but not applied while a group is collapsed — it shrinks to its header — and restored on expand) |
|`z` |Stacking order (higher = in front); set to `max+1` on interaction |
|`style` |Content tiles only — `window` (default) or `bare` |
|`display` |Content tiles only — which field of the `target` to show: a field name, or `body`/`text` for the whole body. Absent = resolve automatically (see //What a tile shows// below). Set from the ⋮ menu |

!! Group (meta) tiles

A tile with `role: group` is a container: its body is a nested `.rr-dash-canvas` enumerating the tiles whose `dash-parent` is this group's title. Because membership is a single field forming a tree, groups nest recursively with no depth limit. A group is positioned, dragged and resized like any tile; the ▸/▾ header control toggles `collapsed`, and its ＋ control adds a nested group. Removing a group re-homes its direct children to the group's own parent (they are not deleted). A group may carry an `icon`: it appears small before the caption while open, and — when the group is collapsed — replaces the header entirely (the icon becomes a click-to-expand button whose tooltip is the caption). Same field-value dispatch as tile display (a tiddler title is transcluded, otherwise the value renders as wikitext).

Tiles — including whole groups — are re-parented by ''dragging'' them onto another container: on release the drop point is hit-tested for the topmost `.rr-dash-canvas`, and if it differs from the tile's current container (and is the same dashboard, and not the tile's own descendant) the tile's `dash-parent`, position and `z` are rewritten. Holding ''Ctrl''/''Cmd'' at the start of the drag ''duplicates'' a content tile instead of moving it — a new tile with the same `target` is created at the drop point and the original is left untouched, so a tiddler may appear on any number of tiles.

!! Tile title scheme

```
$:/config/rimir/dashboard/<dashId>/tiles/<uid>
```

Tiles live under `$:/config/…`, so they sync to disk but stay out of the default tiddler lists.

!! `<$dashboard-drag>` widget

The positioning/interaction widget (used internally by the canvas body).

|!Attribute |!Meaning |
|`tile` |Title of the tile tiddler |
|`x` `y` `w` `h` |Initial geometry in pixels |
|`z` |Initial `z-index` |
|`class` |Class(es) for the box element |
|`move-selector` |CSS selector that starts a move; empty = the whole box |
|`min-width` `min-height` |Resize floor (default 120 / 80) |
|`fit-width` / `fit-height` |`yes` renders the box at auto (shrink-to-fit) width / height (used for collapsed groups, which shrink to their header); otherwise `w` / `h` are applied |
|`container` |Id of the container this tile currently lives in (the group title, or empty for the root canvas) — used to detect re-parenting |
|`dash-id` |The dashboard id — re-parenting is only allowed within the same dashboard |
|`actions` |Action string invoked on a move/resize release //within the same container//, with variables `<<new-x>>` `<<new-y>>` `<<new-w>>` `<<new-h>>` |
|`reparent-actions` |Action string invoked when a move ends over a //different// container, with the above plus `<<new-parent>>` (the target container's id) |
|`copy-actions` |Action string invoked instead of moving when Ctrl/Cmd is held at the start of a move — same variables as `reparent-actions`. Creates a duplicate tile; the original snaps back. Only content tiles set this (groups are not duplicated) |
|`open-actions` |Action string invoked on a plain click (no drag) |
|`ctrl-open-url` |A URL; when set, a ''Ctrl/Cmd-click'' (no drag) opens it in a new browser tab instead of running `open-actions`. Absolute URLs open as-is; a bare host gets `https://` prepended |

Recognised regions inside the box: `.rr-dash-handle` (move surface for window and group tiles), `.rr-dash-resize` (resize grip), `.rr-dash-no-drag` (never starts a drag — buttons, controls, the group-name input). Each `.rr-dash-canvas` carries `data-dash-parent` (its container id) and `data-dash-id` so the widget can hit-test drop targets.

!! What a tile shows (display resolution)

For each content tile the //display field// is resolved in this order (first non-empty wins):

# the tile's own `display` field;
# the first per-dashboard //display rule// (see below) whose `filter` selects the tile's `target`;
# the target has a `_thumbnail_uri` (an uploaded image/PDF thumbnail) → `_thumbnail_uri`;
# the target has non-empty `text` → `text` (its body);
# the target has an `icon` → `icon`;
# otherwise `text`.

The resolved field is then rendered: `text`/`body` transcludes the target's body (unchanged from earlier versions); a `_thumbnail_uri` (or the `_canonical_uri` of an image-typed target) becomes an `<img>` scaled to the tile; otherwise the field's value is read — if it names an existing tiddler (real or shadow, e.g. `icon` → an image/SVG tiddler) that tiddler is transcluded — unless it is itself an uploaded image carrying a `_thumbnail_uri`, in which case its thumbnail is shown rather than the full image — else the value is rendered as wikitext (so an inline-SVG `icon` also works).

!! Display rules (per dashboard)

A display rule is a tiddler tagged <<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard/display-rule">>, conventionally stored at `$:/config/rimir/dashboard/<dashId>/display-rules/<uid>`:

|!Field |!Meaning |
|`dashboard` |The dashboard id the rule applies to |
|`filter` |Evaluated against a tile's `target` (as the input) — e.g. `[tag[Image]]`, `[has[icon]]`, `[field:type[image/png]]`. Write it as a run that //filters its input//, not one that selects from all tiddlers |
|`field` |The field to show when the filter matches |
|`order` |Numeric priority; the lowest-order matching rule wins |

Edit them from the //Display rules// panel (the toolbar button toggles it): each row is a `filter ⇒ field` pair with a delete button, plus an add row.

!! Kind integration (optional)

When [[rimir/kind|$:/plugins/rimir/kind]] is installed and a window tile's `target` is a kind instance (a tiddler with a `kind.type` field), the title bar prefixes the caption with the type's `kind.icon`, using the type's `kind.caption` as hover text. The type definition is located generically with

```
[all[shadows+tiddlers]has[kind.fields]field:kind.type<typeKey>has[kind.icon]]
```

so there is no hard dependency on the kind plugin's own functions — the icon simply does not appear when kind (or the type's icon) is absent. Bare tiles have no title bar and therefore show no icon.

!! Configuration tiddlers

|!Tiddler |!Purpose |
|`$:/config/ViewTemplateBodyFilters/rimir-dashboard` |Body-cascade step that swaps a dashboard's body for the canvas |
|`$:/state/rimir/dashboard/add-target` |Transient input backing the //Add tile// box (also used as a new group's name by //Add group//) |
|`$:/state/rimir/dashboard/add-filter` |Transient input backing the //Add matching// filter box; its text is evaluated with `subfilter` and a tile is created per result |
|`$:/state/rimir/dashboard/clean-filter` |Transient input backing the //Clean// filter box; empty removes all tiles, otherwise removes tiles whose target the filter selects |
|`$:/state/rimir/dashboard/clean-confirm` |`yes` while the //Clean// confirmation is showing |
|`$:/state/rimir/dashboard/popup` |Transient title of the tiddler shown in the //show contents// popup; empty when the popup is closed |
|`$:/config/rimir/dashboard/external-open-fields` |Space-separated list of the target's fields consulted, in order, for a tile's external link (↗ action and Ctrl/Cmd-click). The first non-empty one wins. Defaults to `url _canonical_uri` |
|`$:/config/rimir/dashboard/<dashId>/display-rules/…` |Per-dashboard display-rule tiddlers (see //Display rules// above) |
|`$:/state/rimir/dashboard/rules-open` |`yes` while the //Display rules// panel is open |
|`$:/state/rimir/dashboard/icon-edit` |Title of the group whose icon editor is open; empty when closed |

